OL,3,CPotato farmer could lose 'a couple of
OL,4,Chundred thousand' with warning of
OL,5,Cshortage
OL,7,F"But we never in living memory have we
OL,8,Fhad a wet summer, a wet winter, a wet
OL,9,Fautumn followed by a wet spring, so
OL,10,Fthis is a complete anomaly."
OL,12,FParts of the UK saw the wettest March
OL,13,Fin more than 40 years.
OL,15,FThe Hamilton fields are currently
OL,16,Fwaterlogged meaning that tractors and
OL,17,Fharvesters can't even make it out onto
OL,18,Fthem.
